First Lady Melania Trump and Queen Rania Al-Abdullah visited Excel Academy Public Charter School in Washington DC. They had lunch and discussed their roles in government and the challenges their nations face. They also participated in a listening session with teachers, parents, and students, discussing the school's demographics, mission, and teaching life skills and community engagement. They toured the school and visited active classrooms. Melania Trump emphasized the importance of education in promoting gender equality and empowerment of women. Excel Academy is Washington DC's first public charter school for girls, with a mission to provide girls with a solid academic foundation and enrichment opportunities to prepare them for success in high school and college.